title: Cross Country Roundup: Liberty Union girls place 2nd
text:
Cross Country Roundup: Liberty Union girls place 2nd 10:59 p.m. EDT October 17, 2015 11 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Mid State League at Logan Elm 
Liberty Union was led by race winner Sydnee Mangette (18:56) at the Mid State League tournament on Saturday. Mangette’s teammates Kenley French (3rd, 19:21), Elayna Miracle (8th, 20:46), Alaina Miller (11th, 21:43) and Brittany Schmauch (18th, 22:14) helped the girls to a 2nd place finish with 42 points. 
The Liberty Union boys finished 4th out of seven teams at Logan Elm with 81 points. The Lions were led by race winner Wyatt Gardner (15:56), Kelton French (6th, 16:38), Brook Taylor (11th, 16:58), Nick Ellas (31st, 19:26) and Davis Sodders (36th, 20:23). 
Bloom-Carroll’s girls also competed finishing 5th with 138 points. They were led by Lydia Taylor (20th, 22:55), Sarah Shepard (24th, 24:14), Emma Graham (31st, 24:54), Lynna Freeman (32nd, 24:59) and Natalie Detwiler (41st, 28:30). 
Bloom-Carroll’s boys did not place only having three runners complete the course, Kenny Sherman (29th, 19:18), Jayden Kitchen (30th, 19:19) and Sam Graham (40th, 21:03). Read or Share this story: http://ohne.ws/1RP1BCw MORE STORIES
